Shoulder girdle ( Figs. 17 , 19–20 ). Radial bearing first proterygial basal element of pectoral fin skeleton inserting at mesocondyle much shorter than further anterior basal elements, about 4 times in length of the next anterior element, which is a divided cartilage as typical for male anacanthobatids (see
Weigmann et al. 2014
). First metapterygial basal element extremely long and bearing by far the majority of posterior pectoral radials; the very much shorter second and final metapterygium bearing only two radials laterally and two splitting from its posterior tip.
